1.0.4

  - tiny patch to work with most recent scikit-learn version

1.0.3

  - fix error NMF TypeError after scikit-learn release 1.2.0 (parameter name changed)

  - remove support for creating a vocabulary mapping (merging similar terms);
    now one can (i) use the default one for the existing neuroquery vocabulary,
    (ii) use the empty mapping (do not merge any terms) or (iii) input a
    user-defined vocabulary mapping

  - remove dependency on python-Levenshtein